Package graph.tree.spqr

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractTree<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    Abstract class, extended by SPQR tree and proto SPQR tree
    ProtoSPQRTree<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    Used in the construction of SPQR trees Not a very efficient implementation, needs to be rewritten Can be used for smaller graphs
    Skeleton<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    Each node is associated with a special graph which is called a skeleton of the node It is a simplified version of the original graph where some subgraphs were replaces
    SPQRTree<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    SPQR-trees implicitly represent all embeddings of a graph The triconnected components of a biconnected graph are a system of smaller graphs that describe all of the 2-vertex cuts in the graph.
    SPQRTreeNode<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    Node of the SPQR tree
    TreeEdgeWithContent<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    Class which implements the Edge interface and adds the content attribute Used for constructing SPQR-trees
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    NodeType
    Type of the SPQR tree node
